{"id":117,"date":"2013-08-09T19:11:51","date_gmt":"2013-08-09T19:11:51","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/new.townofdundee.com\/?page_id=117"},"modified":"2026-04-16T12:54:00","modified_gmt":"2026-04-16T16:54:00","slug":"home","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/","title":{"rendered":"Welcome to the Town of Dundee"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] thread-sm:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] thread-lg:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)\">\n<div class=\"[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] thread-lg:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group\/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"flex max-w-full flex-col grow\">\n<div class=\"min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1\" dir=\"auto\" data-message-author-role=\"assistant\" data-message-id=\"29952c53-2805-4666-be29-d24a240fedaf\" data-message-model-slug=\"gpt-5\">\n<div class=\"flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]\">\n<div class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light markdown-new-styling\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<div dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<div class=\"xdj266r x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs x126k92a\">\n<p><strong>Reminder the deadline is approaching!\u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<p class=\"isSelectedEnd\">The deadline to submit your application for a commemorative brick is <strong>April 17th<\/strong>\u2014don\u2019t miss your chance to be part of this meaningful tribute to our veterans.<\/p>\n<p class=\"isSelectedEnd\">Please note: All applications must be submitted through Melissa to complete your purchase.<\/p>\n<p class=\"isSelectedEnd\">If you\u2019re interested in purchasing a brick or have questions about the process, Town Hall is here to help! To request an application or get more information, contact:<br \/>\n863-438-8330 ext. 271<br \/>\n<a href=\"mailto:MGlogowski@townofdundee.com\">MGlogowski@townofdundee.com<\/a><\/p>\n<p>Thank you for helping us preserve and honor the legacy of our veterans. \u2764\ufe0f<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Brick-Fundraiser-Flyer-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Flyer for 2026 &quot;Personalized Military Service Brick Dedication&quot; The flyer invites the public to &quot;Celebrate your loved ones who served this country by dedicating a brick in their honor. Add their name, rand and service years to a brick for display at our Centennial Veterans Memorial Park, May 25, 2026. $65.00 per each personalized brick.. Order forms available at www.townofdundee.com and Town Hall Customer Service Desk. Must be received by Friday, April 17th, 2026&quot; The design features white background with blue writing, with a waving flag element across the top, a row of red and blue alternating stars and the Town of Dundee logo in the top right corner. \" \/><\/p>\n<p>________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span class=\"x1xsqp64 xiy17q3 x1o6pynw x19co3pv xdj266r xjn30re xat24cr x1hb08if x2b8uid\" data-testid=\"emoji\" data-emoji-size=\"16\"><span class=\"xexx8yu xcaqkgz x18d9i69 xbwkkl7 x3jgonx x1bhl96m\">\u00a0 <span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t6f\/1\/16\/1f6ab.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span><span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t50\/1\/16\/1f525.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span> UPDATE: BURN BAN SUSPENSION EXTENDED UNTIL 4\/24 <span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t50\/1\/16\/1f525.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span><span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t6f\/1\/16\/1f6ab.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/h3>\n<p dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Polk County has extended the countywide burn ban suspension until 11:59 p.m. on April 24, 2026. The burn ban was suspended on April 9, 2026. For more information visit <a class=\"x1fey0fg xmper1u x1edh9d7\" href=\"https:\/\/www.polkfl.gov\/...\/polk-county-extends...\/\">https:\/\/www.polkfl.gov\/&#8230;\/polk-county-extends&#8230;\/<\/a><\/p>\n<p>This extension was made by Polk County Fire Chief Shawn Smith, who stated that the decision was based on continuous monitoring of the drought conditions in the area. Residents are encouraged to follow burn safety practices while enjoying recreational fires.<\/p>\n<p>________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/p>\n<p>Dear families,<\/p>\n<p>Polk County Public Schools is once again offering a free summer program specifically designed for incoming kindergartners.<\/p>\n<p>Camp Early Bird will be held from June 3 \u2013 June 25. This free program is being hosted at specific elementary schools in Polk County.<\/p>\n<p>The summer camp is available to incoming kindergarten students enrolling in a PCPS elementary school. Our experienced, certified teachers will use fun activities and learning experiences to prepare these soon-to-be kindergartners for success in the classroom and beyond.<\/p>\n<p>Students must have their own transportation to the camp. Breakfast and lunch will be provided free of charge for all students.<\/p>\n<p>Parents must register their children online. Registration will open on Wednesday, April 15, at 8 a.m. and close on April 29.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Seats are available on a first-come, first-served basis, so make sure to apply early!<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 11.0pt;\">Please visit <a href=\"http:\/\/track.spe.schoolmessenger.com\/f\/a\/4Cdyc5_hSn3SF-ylQNqh-Q~~\/AAAAARA~\/hoEUkuW3fZvk-aF2vQHXoD9Lqg15FU9ux_C57KahAmP0sB55rEyNZnuZhR-JsQUciJlS-FnDuoKHwgl0EVVQlic82oX9pQZfGefNzAM-d2ZkEXbFiVVnbt1nsw0FpX31\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt;\">www.polkschoolsfl.com\/earlybird<\/span><\/a>\u00a0for more information and to access the online registration form.<\/span><\/p>\n<p data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"416\">________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/p>\n<p data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"416\">The Town would like to clarify that the Town Attorney was inadvertently not notified of the April 6, 2026, Town Commission Special Meeting. We take full responsibility for this oversight and want to assure the public that, given the nature of the meeting, there are no legal issues associated with its holding.<\/p>\n<p>We have reviewed our internal processes and are taking steps to ensure proper notification and coordination for all future meetings<\/p>\n<p>We appreciate the public\u2019s understanding and remain committed to maintaining transparency, accountability, and effective communication moving forward.<\/p>\n<p data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"416\">________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"416\"><strong>ANNOUNCEMENT &#8211; DUKE ENERGY<\/strong><\/h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"416\">As part of Duke Energy\u2019s continuing commitment to provide safe and reliable electrical service to its<br \/>\ncommunities, it must invest in the proper care and maintenance of its transmission infrastructure.<br \/>\nPart of this maintenance program involves the vegetation management within their right-of-way<br \/>\ncorridor. To ensure continued reliable electric service, crews will be pruning and, in some<br \/>\ncases, removing trees within the ICLW-1 69kV transmission power line corridor. Affected landowners<br \/>\nwill be notified individually as the project proceeds and prior to work commencing on their property.<br \/>\nAlthough they do not anticipate any power interruptions at this time, should an outage become<br \/>\nnecessary to complete this work, they will notify affected customers in advance. This work is<br \/>\nscheduled to begin in the next few weeks. This notice constitutes the notice required by Florida<br \/>\nStatute 163.3209.<\/p>\n<p data-start=\"149\" data-end=\"416\">________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/p>\n<h4 dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t9\/1\/16\/1f386.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span> <strong>CALLING FOR EVENT VENDORS<\/strong> <span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t9\/1\/16\/1f386.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span><\/h4>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\">\n<div dir=\"auto\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">The Town of Dundee is gearing up for our annual 4th of July Celebration, and we\u2019re looking for amazing vendors to join the fun!<\/span><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\">\n<div dir=\"auto\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">We are currently seeking Craft Vendors, Informational Vendors, and Food Vendors. This is a great opportunity to showcase your products, connect with the community, and be part of one of Dundee\u2019s most exciting annual events! <\/span><span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\" style=\"color: #800080;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t4d\/1\/16\/1f4de.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\"> Interested in participating? Contact Melissa at 863.438.8330 ext. 271 Or e-mail: Events2@townofdundee.com for an application. <\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Spots fill quickly\u2014don\u2019t miss your chance to be part of the celebration!\u00a0<\/span><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\">\n<div dir=\"auto\"><span style=\"color: #00ccff; text-align: center;\">________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/span><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">Public Utilities Notices<\/span><\/h2>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span class=\"x1xsqp64 xiy17q3 x1o6pynw x19co3pv xdj266r xjn30re xat24cr x1hb08if x2b8uid\" data-testid=\"emoji\" data-emoji-size=\"16\"><span class=\"xexx8yu xcaqkgz x18d9i69 xbwkkl7 x3jgonx x1bhl96m\">\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 <\/span><\/span><\/span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.swfwmd.state.fl.us\/business\/epermitting\/district-water-restrictions\"><span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t45\/1\/16\/1f6a8.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span> Modified Phase<\/a><\/strong><\/span><\/span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.swfwmd.state.fl.us\/business\/epermitting\/district-water-restrictions\"> 3<\/a><\/strong><\/span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.swfwmd.state.fl.us\/business\/epermitting\/district-water-restrictions\"> Extreme Water Shortage Restrictions <span class=\"html-span xexx8yu xyri2b x18d9i69 x1c1uobl x1hl2dhg x16tdsg8 x1vvkbs x3nfvp2 x1j61x8r x1fcty0u xdj266r xat24cr xm2jcoa x1mpyi22 xxymvpz xlup9mm x1kky2od\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"xz74otr x15mokao x1ga7v0g x16uus16 xbiv7yw\" src=\"https:\/\/static.xx.fbcdn.net\/images\/emoji.php\/v9\/t45\/1\/16\/1f6a8.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" \/><\/span><\/a><\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/h2>\n<div dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<div class=\"xdj266r x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs x126k92a\">\n<h4 dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Southwest Florida Water Management District&#8217;s (District) Governing Board to declare a Modified Phase III &#8220;Extreme&#8221; Water Shortage due to ongoing drought conditions. All Residents including those on private wells are to follow one-day-per-week watering restrictions with new hours effective are effective from April 3, 2026, through July 1, 2026.<\/span><\/h4>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<h4 dir=\"auto\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Beginning April 3rd, water hours are reduced to Before 4 a.m. or After 8 p.m. Watering days are as follows: Even addresses can water on Tuesdays and Odd addresses can water on Thursdays. Properties less than one (1) acre in size may only use one of these windows. Properties over one (1) acre may only water before 4am or after 8pm. <\/span><\/h4>\n<h4 dir=\"auto\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Let\u2019s all do our part to protect our water supply!\u00a0 See additional information below!<\/span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/home\/phase-iii-water-shortage-1-1\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10610\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-10610 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Phase-III-water-shortage-1-1-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Phase-III-water-shortage-1-1-232x300.jpg 232w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Phase-III-water-shortage-1-1-791x1024.jpg 791w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Phase-III-water-shortage-1-1-768x995.jpg 768w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Phase-III-water-shortage-1-1-1186x1536.jpg 1186w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Phase-III-water-shortage-1-1.jpg 1483w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 232px) 100vw, 232px\" \/><\/a>_______________________________________________________________________________________<\/span><\/h4>\n<h4 dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\"><strong data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"38\">Stay Up to Date on Town Events!\u00a0<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" data-start=\"40\" data-end=\"180\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Looking for information about upcoming Town events? Visit the <strong data-start=\"102\" data-end=\"127\">Town of Dundee Events<\/strong> page located under <strong data-start=\"147\" data-end=\"162\">Quick Links; <\/strong>this page is regularly updated with details about Dundee events happening throughout the year. It\u2019s the best place to find dates, times, locations, and other important information.<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" data-start=\"40\" data-end=\"180\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">If you are looking for events happening on a <strong data-start=\"404\" data-end=\"421\">specific date<\/strong>, be sure to check-out the <strong data-start=\"448\" data-end=\"474\">Dundee Events Calendar<\/strong> located under <strong data-start=\"489\" data-end=\"506\">Our Community<\/strong>, where you can view events and meetings scheduled throughout the year.<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" data-start=\"330\" data-end=\"447\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Be sure to check-out the events page and the Dundee Events Calendar, these pages regularly so you don\u2019t miss out on all the great things happening in the Town of Dundee!<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" data-start=\"330\" data-end=\"447\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><span style=\"color: #008080;\">______________________________________________________________________________________________<\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>AUTISM AWARENESS MONTH<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Join us in recognizing Autism Awareness Month this April as we celebrate inclusion, understanding, and the unique strengths of individuals on the autism spectrum. Together, we can help build a more supportive and connected community.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light markdown-new-styling\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">\u00a0 <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/home\/aam-12-1\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10597\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-10597\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/aam-12-1-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Graphic with the message \u201cWe are celebrating Autism Awareness Month\u201d in bold, colorful text. The word \u201cAUTISM\u201d is prominently displayed, with a bright, multicolored puzzle-pattern ribbon forming the letter \u201cI.\u201d The Town logo is placed in the banner area next to the word \u201cWe.\u201d The design features vibrant colors like blue, green, red, and yellow, and includes the text \u201cAll of April\u201d on a light background.\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" srcset=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/aam-12-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/aam-12-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/aam-12-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/aam-12-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/aam-12-1.jpg 1920w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] thread-sm:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] thread-lg:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)\">\n<div class=\"[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] thread-lg:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group\/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"flex max-w-full flex-col grow\">\n<div class=\"min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1\" dir=\"auto\" data-message-author-role=\"assistant\" data-message-id=\"29952c53-2805-4666-be29-d24a240fedaf\" data-message-model-slug=\"gpt-5\">\n<div class=\"flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]\">\n<div class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light markdown-new-styling\">\n<div class=\"x14z9mp xat24cr x1lziwak x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\">\n<div dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<p>________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Town Wide Clean-Up<\/span><\/h2>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Join us for the Dundee Town-Wide Cleanup on Saturday, April 18th from 9:00 a.m. \u2013 12:00 p.m.!<\/span><\/h4>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Let\u2019s work together to keep our community clean and beautiful! Multiple dumpster locations will be available throughout town (see flyer for locations) where residents can bring household garbage for disposal.<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"color: #008000;\">Want to make an even bigger impact? Sign up to volunteer and help with litter collection around town! Contact Melissa at (863) 438-8330 ext. 271 or MGlogowski@townofdundee.com to sign up to volunteer. This event is proudly sponsored by the Dundee Tree Board, Keep Polk County Beautiful, and Trash Taxi. Let\u2019s come together and show our Dundee pride \u2014 we hope to see you there!<\/span><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/event\/town-wide-clean-up\/arbor-day-flyer-4-18-2026-3\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10485\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-10485\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Arbor-Day-Flyer-4.18.2026-1-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Flyer for the Dundee Tree Board\u2019s \u201cCelebrate Arbor Day! Town-Wide Cleanup &amp; Dumpster Day\u201d event. The flyer features green and brown text with a tree graphic in the center and a green dumpster image on the right. It lists the event details as Saturday, April 18, 2026, from 9:00 a.m. to 12:00 p.m. Join the Cleanup Crew! We\u2019re looking for awesome volunteers (families welcome!) to help with garbage collection routes during our Town Wide Cleanup Day. Let\u2019s work together to keep our town shining! To Volunteer contact Melissa at (863) 438-8330 ext. 271 or MGlogowski@townofdundee.com Dumpster locations include: \u2022 Henderson Park \u2013 413 Martin Luther King Street (Misc. Trash\/Bulk) \u2022 Lake Marie \u2013 Scenic Hwy (between the walking trail and Church on the Hill) (Misc. Trash\/Bulk &amp; Tires) \u2022 Town Hall \u2013 202 E. Main Street, back parking lot (Misc. Trash\/Bulk &amp; Electronics) \u2022 Public Works Barn \u2013 1500 Race Road (Appliances) Accepted items include construction materials, appliances (with freon and doors removed), air conditioners (freon removed), miscellaneous household garbage (no food), tires (rims removed), electronics (batteries removed), and garage items. Refused items include paints, concrete, household chemicals, batteries, vehicle fluids, shingles, asbestos, and car parts. Sponsors listed at the bottom are Keep Polk County Beautiful, the Town of Dundee Tree Board, and Trash Taxi.\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Arbor-Day-Flyer-4.18.2026-1-232x300.jpg 232w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Arbor-Day-Flyer-4.18.2026-1-791x1024.jpg 791w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Arbor-Day-Flyer-4.18.2026-1-768x994.jpg 768w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Arbor-Day-Flyer-4.18.2026-1-1187x1536.jpg 1187w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Arbor-Day-Flyer-4.18.2026-1-1583x2048.jpg 1583w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Arbor-Day-Flyer-4.18.2026-1.jpg 1700w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 232px) 100vw, 232px\" \/><\/a><br \/>\n________________________________________________________________________________________________<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div dir=\"auto\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">FOR UTILITY DISRUPTION PLEASE CONTACT:<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\">During Office Hours: (863) 438-8330 Option 1<br \/>\nFor After Hours, please contact our Emergency On-Call #: (863) 439-7966<\/h4>\n<h4 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>_______________________________________________________________________________________<\/strong><\/h4>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full break-words light markdown-new-styling\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<h3><strong>We\u2019re Looking for Community-Minded Volunteers!<\/strong><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<p>The Town of Dundee is currently seeking dedicated residents to Serve on the Dundee Tree Board!<\/p>\n<p data-start=\"98\" data-end=\"359\">The Tree Board plays an important role in helping shape a greener, more beautiful Dundee. Members work together to guide tree planting and preservation efforts, promote proper tree care, and support community events that highlight the value of our urban forest.<\/p>\n<p data-start=\"361\" data-end=\"528\">From enhancing public spaces to educating residents on the importance of trees, the Tree Board helps keep our town healthy, vibrant, and sustainable for years to come.\u00a0Interested in making a difference? We\u2019d love to have you join us! Please contact the Melissa Glogowski, in the Town Clerks office at 863.438.8330 ext. 271 or MGlogowski@townofdundee.com to request a board application.<\/p>\n<p>#Dundeeonetownoneteam.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/home\/tree-board-members-needed-flyer-2\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10667\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-10667 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Tree-Board-Members-Needed-Flyer-1-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"Flyer from the Town of Dundee seeking Tree Board members. The design features a large green tree with visible roots on the right side and the Town of Dundee logo at the top left. Bold text reads \u201cWe Are Looking for Tree Board Members.\u201d Below, it asks \u201cWhat makes a good Tree Board member?\u201d followed by listed qualities: a passion for the community; desire to improve and beautify the town through tree and forestry management; interest in educating and involving the community on the importance of trees; and willingness to participate in board meetings and events. Contact information for Melissa Glogowski, including phone number and email, appears in a green circle at the top right.\" width=\"232\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Tree-Board-Members-Needed-Flyer-1-232x300.jpg 232w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Tree-Board-Members-Needed-Flyer-1-791x1024.jpg 791w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Tree-Board-Members-Needed-Flyer-1-768x994.jpg 768w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Tree-Board-Members-Needed-Flyer-1-1187x1536.jpg 1187w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Tree-Board-Members-Needed-Flyer-1-1583x2048.jpg 1583w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Tree-Board-Members-Needed-Flyer-1-scaled.jpg 1978w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 232px) 100vw, 232px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<h3 data-start=\"61\" data-end=\"225\">___________________________________________________________________________<\/h3>\n<p data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"254\">The Town of Dundee has introduced <strong data-start=\"61\" data-end=\"80\">Ordinance(s) 25-07, 25-08, and 25-09<\/strong>\u00a0establishing a <strong data-start=\"97\" data-end=\"125\">Business Impact Estimate<\/strong>\u00a0to enhance transparency and assess local business effects. Learn how this ordinance supports informed decision-making.<\/p>\n<p data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"254\"><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Town-of-Dundee-BIE-Ordinance-25-07-2nd-Reading.docx\">Town of Dundee BIE- Ordinance 25-07 2nd Reading<\/a><\/p>\n<p data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"254\"><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Town-of-Dundee-BIE-Ordinance-25-08-2nd-Reading.docx\">Town of Dundee BIE- Ordinance 25-08 2nd Reading<\/a><\/p>\n<p data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"254\"><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/SBC-Town-of-Dundee-BIE-Ordinance-25-09-12-10-25.docx\">SBC Town of Dundee BIE- Ordinance 25-09 12-10-25<\/a><\/p>\n<p data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"254\"><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/home\/town-of-dundee-bie-ordinance-26-01-2nd-reading\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10371\">Town of Dundee BIE- Ordinance 26-01 2nd Reading<\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"254\">_____________________________________________________________________________________________ <strong data-start=\"115\" data-end=\"163\">2026 Holiday Sanitation Collection Schedules<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"254\">The Town of Dundee\u2019s 2026 Holiday Sanitation Collection Schedules are now available. This schedule outlines sanitation pickup changes for all holidays throughout the entire year. \u00a0Please review the flyer below and plan ahead for adjusted collection days.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-start=\"49\" data-end=\"196\"><strong>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/home\/2026-residential-sanitation-schedule\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10306\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10306\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Residential-Sanitation-Schedule-300x154.png\" alt=\"white flyer with orange, green and yellow border, town to dundee logo, sky and sanitation truck. wording states Town of Dundee holiday schedule sanitation department 2026. Memorial Day 5\/25\/2026 Monday will be collected on Tuesday 5\/26\/2026 Tuesday will be collected on Wednesday 5\/27\/2026 Wednesday will be collected on Thursday 5\/28\/2026 Juneteenth 6\/19\/2026- No Changes to collections, No Special Collections 4th of July 7\/4\/2026 No Changes to collections, No Special Collections Labor Day 9\/7\/2026 Monday will be collected on Tuesday 9\/8\/2026 Tuesday will be collected on Wednesday 9\/9\/2026 Wednesday will be collected on Thursday 9\/10\/2026. Veterans Day 11\/11\/2026 Monday 11\/9\/2026 No Changes Tuesday 11\/10\/2026 No Changes. Veterans Day 11\/11\/2026. Wednesday 11\/11\/2026 will be collected on Thursday 11\/12\/2026. Thanksgi11ing 11\/26\/2026 No Changes to Collections, No Special Collections. Christmas 12\/25\/2026 No Changes to Collections, No Special Collections. New Years Day 1\/1\/2027 No Changes to Collections, No Special Collections \" width=\"493\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Residential-Sanitation-Schedule-300x154.png 300w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Residential-Sanitation-Schedule-1024x525.png 1024w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Residential-Sanitation-Schedule-768x394.png 768w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Residential-Sanitation-Schedule.png 1282w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 493px) 100vw, 493px\" \/><\/a> \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/home\/2026-republic-holiday-collection-schedule\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10307\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-10307\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Republic-Holiday-Collection-Schedule-232x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"213\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Republic-Holiday-Collection-Schedule-232x300.jpg 232w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Republic-Holiday-Collection-Schedule-791x1024.jpg 791w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Republic-Holiday-Collection-Schedule-768x994.jpg 768w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Republic-Holiday-Collection-Schedule-1187x1536.jpg 1187w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Republic-Holiday-Collection-Schedule-1583x2048.jpg 1583w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026-Republic-Holiday-Collection-Schedule.jpg 1700w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 213px) 100vw, 213px\" \/><\/a>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0<\/strong><\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">Join the Town of Dundee Citizen Visioning Committee<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-8635 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Vision-Committee-Flyer-169x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"169\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Vision-Committee-Flyer-169x300.jpg 169w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Vision-Committee-Flyer-576x1024.jpg 576w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Vision-Committee-Flyer-768x1365.jpg 768w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Vision-Committee-Flyer-864x1536.jpg 864w, https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Vision-Committee-Flyer.jpg 1080w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 169px) 100vw, 169px\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you are interested in shaping the vision for the future of our Town, consider joining the Visioning Committee by filling out the application and returning it to the Town Clerk, Erica Anderson, at eanderson@townofdundee.com. To join, you must either reside in the Town of Dundee or be a property owner and be appointed by the Town Commission.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/Dundee-Board-Application-Fillable-2021-1.pdf\">Dundee Board Application- Fillable 2021<\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>VISIONING COMMITTEE AGENDAS<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">September 20, 2024 &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024-0920-Agenda-Visioning.pdf\">2024 0920 Agenda Visioning<\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">October 25, 2024 &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024-1025-Agenda-Visioning.pdf\">2024 1025 Agenda Visioning<\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">November 22, 2024 &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024-1122-Agenda-Visioning.pdf\">2024 1122 Agenda Visioning<\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>VISIONING COMMITTEE MINUTES<\/strong><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">September 20, 2024 &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/20240920-Visioning-Minutes-DRAFT.docx\">20240920 Visioning Minutes DRAFT<\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">October 25, 2024 &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/20241025-Visioning-Minutes-REVIEWED.docx\">20241025 Visioning Minutes REVIEWED<\/a><\/p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">____________________________________________________________<\/h3>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">RECORDS CUSTODIAN<\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Town Hall<br \/>\n202 East Main Street<br \/>\n(863) 438-8330, ext. 258<br \/>\n<a href=\"mailto:EAnderson@townofdundee.com\">EAnderson@townofdundee.com<\/a><br \/>\n(See Florida Statutes 119.01)<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Reminder the deadline is approaching!\u00a0 The deadline to submit your application for a commemorative brick is April 17th\u2014don\u2019t miss your chance to be part of this meaningful tribute to our [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":11,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-117","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/117","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/11"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=117"}],"version-history":[{"count":742,"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/117\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":10671,"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/117\/revisions\/10671"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/townofdundee.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=117"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}